{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17620402","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17620402"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:43:03+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:43:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16626"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16626","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16626"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.65,0.03,0,0.25]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9317"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76350"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9317","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9317"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16626"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61859"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1353"},{"type":"tags","id":"1627"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4932"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5316"},{"type":"tags","id":"10135"},{"type":"tags","id":"10193"},{"type":"tags","id":"10552"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22090"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22458"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76350","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76350"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 28-year-old woman presents with excessive facial hair growth. She is diagnosed with polycystic ovary syndrome and prescribed finasteride off-label to manage her hirsutism.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the medication\u0027s primary mechanism of action?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Reduces testosterone production","Inhibits 5-alpha reductase enzyme","Stimulates hair follicle regression directly","Increases oestrogen levels","Blocks androgen receptors"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EFinasteride works by \u003Cstrong\u003Einhibiting\u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003E5-alpha reductase enzyme\u003C/strong\u003E, which normally converts testosterone to dihydrotestosterone (DHT). By reducing DHT levels, finasteride can help treat conditions that are DHT-dependent, such as hirsutism in women with polycystic ovary syndrome.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduces testosterone production\u003C/strong\u003E - Finasteride does not affect testosterone production, but rather prevents its conversion to DHT.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EStimulates hair follicle regression directly\u003C/strong\u003E - Finasteride does not directly affect hair follicles, but works by reducing DHT levels which can decrease unwanted hair growth.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreases oestrogen levels\u003C/strong\u003E - Finasteride does not have any direct effect on oestrogen levels in the body.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocks androgen receptors\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes the mechanism of anti-androgens such as spironolactone, not finasteride.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDHT is more potent than testosterone at the androgen receptor. By reducing DHT levels, finasteride decreases androgen-mediated effects in DHT-sensitive tissues.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Finasteride inhibits 5-alpha reductase enzyme which converts testosterone to dihydrotestosterone.","Dihydrotestosterone is more potent than testosterone and contributes to hirsutism in women with polycystic ovary syndrome.","By reducing dihydrotestosterone levels, finasteride can treat hirsutism in women."],"references":["Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/","Lakryc EM, Motta EL, Soares JM Jr, Haidar MA, de Lima GR, Baracat EC. The benefits of finasteride for hirsute women with polycystic ovary syndrome or idiopathic hirsutism. Gynecol Endocrinol. 2003;17(1):57-63."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61859"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16626"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61859","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61859"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-03T08:59:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-03T08:59:57+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9317"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76350"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}}